metadata.description: i went out to dinner with some friends and recalled some of the debauchery i got into last year, with one person in particular.

lyrics.text:
You wanted a Camaro 

You wanted to be cool 

But your parents got you a mustang 

And you took that thing to school 

Then you went all the way 

All the way 

Way out to California to realize those dreams 

The ones where you’re the center of a big amc screen 

Yeah you wanna go all the way

All the way 

And you’ve got angles in common with Anna de armas and Marion cotillard 

And our lives are evolving working at a restaurant until next year cause that’s when your movie starts 

I used to throw big parties 

And I probably will again 

There were strangers in my patio and we snuck away from them and we went all the way 

All the way 

Yeah we ran into my closet 

And we turned off all the lights 

That sensory deprivation was some of the best sex of my life 

I’ve got a lot to say

Lot to say

Oh this life’s been so crazy that these nights keep erasing but some I just can’t ever forget 

And when dear Isabella thinks of how that night developed I hope it feels a bit warmer in her head 

I just wanna make out on my couch

Find a new nothing to talk about 

I just wanna make out on my couch

Find some inspiration in your mouth
